Description: production-grade process manager for Python services
 viper keeps long-running Python services alive on Linux servers:
 start/stop/restart, rolling reload, multi-worker apps, per-worker
 memory limits with automatic restart, crash auto-restart with
 exponential backoff, log capture and tailing, and a state journal
 that lets the daemon re-attach to running apps after a crash.
 .
 It only ever manages processes it spawned itself and never
 interferes with other processes on the system.
